basics.name: Jared Au
basics.label: Student
basics.summary: I am a senior studying computer engineering at the University of Hawaii at Manoa. I am currently a student intern at NIWC (Naval Information Warfare Center) formerly known as SPAWAR. My expected date of graduation is Spring 2020.

education.area: Computer Engineering (expected Spring, 2020) | Minor in Business Administration

work.summary: Worked on various projects within Communications branch, and Infrastructure branch
highlights: Grounding Rod repair at Kaneohe Marine Corps Base, directed ground logistics and performed basic engineering tasks
P-013 Building project for NIOC Command, performed tech writing and installation supervision
H4H Division Procurement, coordinated procurement efforts, working with various vendors and contacts to secure equipment and supplies for H4H personnel

awards.title: UH Manoa Regents Scholarship
awards.summary: Regents Scholarships are awarded to 20 outstanding freshmen who receive an SAT total score of at least 1340 or ACT combined score of at least 29, maintain at least a 3.5 GPA in academic subjects in high school, and whose extracurricular achievements are shown to be remarkable.

awards.title: Skills USA Networking First Place (State)
awards.summary: Skills USA is a competition for students in Industrial Arts classes, I competed in the Networking competition which consists of: Cable making, Network Configuration, and Support.

awards.title: NSA Stokes Education Program
awards.summary: The Stokes Education Program is designed to offer students a fully paid scholarship to any college of their choice, along with a yearly stipend and salary, with the obligation to work for the NSA for 1.5x College Duration upon graduation. I ended up declining this scholarship to accept the Manoa Regents Scholarship instead.
